--- body ---
## Context

Overnight autonomous orchestration runs mix two failure modes that look
identical to the supervising human but are structurally very different:

- **Trivial stoppages** — the harness asked for permission on a tool call
  the user has implicitly authorised (the tenth `gh pr create` of the night).
  Fixable via the allowlist in `.claude/settings.json`.
- **Hard stoppages** — the agent genuinely needs input: an author decision,
  a failing test, a `/verify-gate` REROLL, a circuit-breaker kill.

The current ticket log has five verbs: `created`, `status`, `claimed`,
`released`, `note`. None encode "agent paused and waited for a human signal".
All stoppages fold into free-form `note` lines or are lost.

Motivating case: ticket 0017 (paper reconsideration) in the cadens
project — the overnight orchestration run stopped multiple times and the
log gave no signal about which stops were trivial vs. genuine.

## Actions

1. **Write `~/.claude/skills/harness-rules/tickets.md`.**
   Document the full verb set including the new `bump` verb. Place alongside
   workflow.md, git.md, coding.md, state.md.

   Verb table addition:
   ```
   bump {category} — {detail}
   ```
   Categories (closed set):
   - `permission` — harness blocked a tool call awaiting user approval
   - `author-decision` — agent judged a call non-autonomous and stopped
   - `test-failure` — `make` / pytest / CI failed
   - `verify-reroll` — `/verify-gate` returned REROLL or ESCALATE
   - `circuit-breaker` — orchestrator killed the agent (timeout, ping-pong)

2. **Update `~/.claude/tickets/tools/go/main.go`** to accept `bump` as a
   valid verb and validate the category against the closed set. Reject
   unknown categories at commit time.

   The current validator uses a loose regex for log lines
   (`timestamp actor verb [anything]`). Extend it to parse the verb token
   and, when it is `bump`, validate the next token against the five
   categories above.

   Add a test case: a line `2026-04-23T09:00Z claude bump permission —
   awaiting gh pr create` should parse cleanly; a line
   `... bump unknown-category — ...` should fail with a clear error.

3. **Update the orchestrator skill** (`~/.claude/skills/orchestrator`)
   to emit `bump circuit-breaker` when a circuit breaker fires (agent
   timeout, ping-pong detector, redirect ban).

4. **Update the `/verify-gate` skill** to emit `bump verify-reroll` in
   the REROLL path.

5. **Add a bump tally to the orchestrator wrap-up.** After all waves,
   print a summary like:

   ```
   Ticket 0017: 12 bumps (9 permission, 1 author-decision, 2 test-failure)
     → 75% trivial — next allowlist pass should absorb them
   ```

6. (Optional / defer) Update `ticket-claim` / `ticket-close` skills to
   emit `bump author-decision` when an agent calls `AskUserQuestion`.
   Requires passing ticket ID through agent prompts, which they currently
   do not.

## Test (first TDD red step)

In `~/.claude/tickets/tools/go/`: add a test case that:
- A log line `2026-04-23T09:00Z claude bump permission — awaiting gh pr create`
  parses cleanly.
- A line `2026-04-23T09:00Z claude bump unknown-category — foo` fails
  validation with an error naming the valid category set.

Existing closed tickets have no `bump` lines — that is fine. The validator
must not flag their absence.

## Exit criteria

- `~/.claude/skills/harness-rules/tickets.md` exists, §Verbs lists `bump` with its 5
  categories.
- erg validator (Go) accepts `bump {category} — {detail}` and rejects
  unknown categories; test cases cover both.
- At least one skill (`/verify-gate`) emits `bump verify-reroll` in the
  REROLL path, proving the end-to-end flow.
- Orchestrator wrap-up prints a bump-category tally at the end of an
  autonomous run.
- No breakage of existing ticket validation.

## Non-goals

- Changing `%erg` to v2. This is an additive verb.
- Retroactively annotating closed tickets.
- Instrumenting every agent prompt path — focus on the three highest-signal
  points: permission blocks, verify-gate REROLL, circuit breakers.
- Replacing the `note` verb. `bump` is additive.

## Relationships

- Supersedes cadens ticket 0019 (same spec, wrong repo).
- Depends on nothing; can start immediately.
